editions published between  and  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide tennessee senators   portraits of leadership in a century of change by william h frist book  editions published in  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide based on indepth research and personal interviews tennessee senators  tells the life stories of seventeen us senators exploring each mans motivation to enter public service and his place in tennessee national and world history and politics the hope factor  engaging the church in the hivaids crisis book  edition published in  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide cuando no hay tiempo que perder  el único médico del senado revela todo lo que hay que saber sobre el bioterrorismo by william h frist book  editions published in  in spanish and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide when every moment counts spanish meet the press visual  editions published in  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide martin mcguinness discusses historic peace agreement in northern ireland with ira steven parrish donna shalala bill frist and henry waxman analyze the tobacco industry as smoking in youth gains momentum john kasich discusses social security and the future of president bill clinton william safire david maraniss and stuart taylor provide insight and analyzes on whether or not ken starr will recommend impeachment for president clinton meet the press visual  edition published in  in english and held by  worldcat member libraries worldwide on this edition of meet the press bill frist and sue bailey discuss biological and chemical warfare and the recent anthrax scares an interview with the taliban ambassador to pakistan suhail shaheen an interview with attorney general john ashcroft and an interview with benazir bhutto about protests in pakistan as a result of a us presence in afghanistan meet the press visual  edition published in  in english and held by  worldcat membe